NEWS(1)                    IRSH Commands                    NEWS(1)

NAME
    news - fetch security news stories from TechCrunch with summaries

SYNOPSIS
    news [OPTIONS]

DESCRIPTION
    Fetches the latest security news stories from TechCrunch's security category,
    displaying article titles, summaries extracted from the full articles, and links.

OPTIONS
    -n, --num NUMBER
        Number of stories to fetch (1-50, default: 1)

    -s, --sort TYPE
        Sort order for articles: 'recent' or 'older' (default: recent)

    -f, --format TYPE
        Output format:
            brief    - Shows ~100 character summary (default)
            detailed - Shows ~400 character summary for more context

    -h, --help
        Show help message and exit

EXAMPLES
    Fetch the latest security story with brief summary:
        $ news

    Fetch 5 recent stories with detailed summaries:
        $ news -n 5 -f detailed

    Fetch 3 older stories with brief summaries:
        $ news -n 3 -s older

OUTPUT FORMAT
    Brief format:
        [#] Article Title
            Summary text (truncated to ~100 chars)...
            https://link.to/article

    Detailed format:
        [#] Article Title
            Summary text (truncated to ~400 chars)...
            https://link.to/article

NOTES
    - The command fetches each article individually to extract summaries
    - Internet connection is required
    - May take several seconds when fetching multiple articles
    - Uses timeout of 5 seconds per article fetch

SEE ALSO
    weather(1), fortune(1)